> This Stir-Fried Honey Sesame Beef Noodles is a crowd pleaser and is one to get the family round the dinner table for. Super simple to make, and easily customised to suit the kids too.

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the noodles.

Trim and peel the @carrot{1}. Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length of the carrot, stopping at the core.

Cut the @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g} into thirds. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @egg noodle nest{125%g} and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the mince is cooked, transfer it to a #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

Wipe out your (now empty) frying pan and return to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @?oil{}.

Once hot, add the Tenderstem® and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}, then add the carrot ribbons and garlic and stir-fry for ~{30%seconds} more.

Add a splash of water, then cover with a #lid{} (or foil) and allow to cook until tender, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper.

== Sauce ==

While the veg cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine the @soy sauce{25%ml}, @ketjap manis{50%g}, @honey{15%g}, @tomato ketchup{1.5%tbsp} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

== Assembly ==

Once the veg is cooked, add the cooked mince and noodles to the pan.

Pour in the sticky sauce and stir together until piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When ready, share the honey beef noodles between your #bowls{}.

Enjoy!